The '''3rd Division''' ({{lang-no|3. divisjon}}) is a former unit in the [[Norwegian Army]], responsible for the defence of [[Agder]] and [[Rogaland]].
Following the outbreak of the [[Second World War]], the 3rd Division was set up to guard Norway's neutrality position in Agder and Rogaland. During the [[Operation Weserübung|German attack on Norway]], from 9 April 1940, the troops of the 3rd Division were not prepared for such a development, and surrendered after less than a week of the German attack, on 15 April.<ref name=kin>{{cite book|title=Krigen i Norge 1940. Operasjonene i Kristiansand–Setesdals-avsnittet |first=Wilhelm |last=Faye |authorlink=Wilhelm Faye |year=1953 |publisher=Forsvarets Krigshistoriske Avdeling / Gyldendal |language=Norwegian |pages=15–26, 192–198 215}}</ref><ref name=NOU1979-47>{{cite book| |title=Rapport fra den militære undersøkelseskommisjon av 1946 |url=https://www.nb.no/items/URN:NBN:no-nb_digibok_2007071601074 |pages=84–92 |language=Norwegian|accessdate=7 October 2018}}</ref>
The commander of 3rd Division during the period 1935 to 1947, was [[Major General]] [[Einar Liljedahl]].<ref name=hvem-Liljedahl>{{cite encyclopedia|year=1948|title=Liljedahl Einar |encyclopedia=[[Hvem er hvem?]]|editor1-first=Harald |editor1-last=Gram |editor1-link=Harald Gram |editor2-last=Steenstrup |editor2-first= Bjørn|publisher=Aschehoug|location=Oslo|url=http://runeberg.org/hvemerhvem/1948/0322.html|page=322 |language=Norwegian|accessdate=7 October 2018}}</ref>
