{{merge from|Al-Qaeda involvement in the Middle East|discuss=Talk:Al-Qaeda involvement in Asia#Proposed merge with Al-Qaeda involvement in the Middle East|date=October 2017}} '''[[Al Qaeda]] involvement in Asia''' . It is believed that members of Al-Qaeda are in hiding along the border of [[Afghanistan]] and northwest sections of [[Pakistan]].
On February 3, 2009, the government of [[Saudi Arabia]] published a [[Saudi most wanted list|list of 85 suspected terrorists]].<ref name=NYTimes2009-02-03> {{cite news | url=https://www.nytimes.com/2009/02/04/world/middleeast/04saudi.html?ref=world | title=Saudis Issue List of 85 Terrorism Suspects | work=[[The New York Times]] | author=Robert Worth | date=2009-02-03 | accessdate=2009-02-03 | quote= }} </ref><ref name=AsharqAlawsat2009-02-06> {{cite news |url=http://aawsat.com/english/news.asp?section=3&id=15638 |title=A Clear Generation Gap in Saudi Most Wanted List |publisher=[[Asharq Alawsat]] |author=Mshari Al-Zaydi |date=2009-02-06 |accessdate=2009-02-06 |quote= |deadurl=bot: unknown |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100528050308/http://www.aawsat.com/english/news.asp?section=3 |archivedate=2010-05-28 |df= }} </ref><ref name=AsharqAlawsat2009-02-05> {{cite news | url=http://aawsat.com/english/news.asp?section=1&id=15626 | title=Al-Qaeda Using Iran as Base of Operations | publisher=[[Asharq Alawsat]] | author=Turki Al-Saheil | date=2009-02-05 | accessdate=2009-02-06 | quote= }} [https://www.webcitation.org/query?url=http%3A%2F%2Faawsat.com%2Fenglish%2Fnews.asp%3Fsection%3D3%26id%3D15626&date=2009-02-06 mirror] </ref><ref name=SaudiGazetteSaudiMostWanted2009-02-03> {{cite news |url=http://www.saudigazette.com.sa/index.cfm?method=home.regcon&contentID=2009020328293 |title=85 on Saudi wanted list of militants |publisher=[[Saudi Gazette]] |author= |date=2009-02-03 |accessdate=2009-02-03 |quote=Al-Arabiya satellite news channel said the statement identified one of the militants, Saleh Al-Qaraawi, as the leader of Al-Qaeda in Saudi Arabia. |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090207181650/http://www.saudigazette.com.sa/index.cfm?method=home.regcon&contentID=2009020328293 |archivedate=2009-02-07 |df= }} </ref> One key aspect of its international involvement has been to make alliances, which are often "underutilized.".<ref>{{cite journal |journal=Terrorism and Political Violence |volume=27 |issue= |year=2015 |title=Hurdles to International Terrorist Alliances: Lessons From al Qaeda's Experience |doi=10.1080/09546553.2014.993466 |author=Tricia Bacon |pages=}}</ref>
The Saudi government believed that all of these men were living outside of Saudi Arabia, and encouraged them to surrender themselves at the closest Saudi Embassy. Many of those named on the list were believed to be in Asia.{{citation needed|date=July 2015}}
