{{Infobox theatre|name=Norwid Theatre in Jelenia Góra|native_name=Teatr im. Cypriana Kamila Noriwda w Jeleniej Górze|native_name_lang=pl|image=Teatr im C.K.Norwida w Jeleniej Górze.jpg|image_size=274|image_alt=Norwid Theatre in Jelenia Góra|caption=Entrance to Norwid Theatre|address=Wojska Polskiego St. 36|city=[[Jelenia Góra]]|country=[[Poland]]|architect=Alfred Daehmel|owner=|capacity=|type=dramatic theatre|opened=1905|reopened=|website={{URL|http://teatrnorwida.pl/|Theatre website}}}}

The '''Cyprian Norwid Theatre''' in [[Jelenia Góra]] ({{lang-pl|Teatr im. Cypriana Kamila Norwida w Jeleniej Górze}}) is a [[Poland|Polish]] [[Drama|dramatic theatre]] founded in 1945. The Norwid Theatre in Jelenia Góra has two stages: Main Stage (540 seats) and Studio Stage (100 seats).<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.theatre-architecture.eu/pl/db/?theatreId=276&detail=params|title=Theatre database / STRONA GŁÓWNA|website=www.theatre-architecture.eu|language=en|access-date=2017-04-14}}</ref> The theatre is named after [[Cyprian Norwid]].

Polish actress and stage director [[Alina Obidniak]] was [[intendant]] of Norwid Theatre in years 1973-1988 and in 2000. Obidniak invited many renowned theatre directors to Jelenia Góra, including [[Krystian Lupa]], [[Mikołaj Grabowski]], [[Henryk Tomaszewski (mime)|Henryk Tomaszewski]], [[Adam Hanuszkiewicz]], [[Maja Kleczewska]] and Jean-Marie Pradier. She travelled with theatre ensamble to East Germany, Hungary, Italy, Venezuela, Colombia, Panama and Costa Rica.

