In [[Greece]] the all-numeric form for dates is in the little [[endianness]] order of "day month year".  Years can be written with 2 or 4 digits. For example, either 24/5/2004 or 24/5/04.

The [[12-hour notation]] is used in verbal communication, but the [[24-hour format]] is also used along with the 12-hour notation in writing.  The [[minutes]] are usually written with two [[Numerical digit|digits]]; the hour numbers are written with or without a leading zero.

