'''Mondercange communal council''' ({{lang-fr|Conseil communal de Mondercange}}) is the [[Local government|local council]] for the [[Communes of Luxembourg|commune]] of [[Mondercange]], in southern [[Luxembourg]].
It consists of eleven members, elected every six years by [[proportional representation]]. The last elections were held on 9 October 2005, and resulted in a victory for the [[Luxembourg Socialist Workers' Party]] (LSAP). In the ''[[Collège échevinal (Luxembourg)|collège échevinal]]'', the LSAP forms a coalition with the [[Christian Social People's Party]], who have the second-largest contingent, under the leadership of LSAP [[Mayor of Mondercange|mayor]] [[Dan Kersch]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.mondercange.lu/html/politique/conseil.html |title=Le conseil communal |accessdate=2008-02-12 |date= |publisher=Commune of Mondercange |language=fr |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070613105659/http://www.mondercange.lu/html/politique/conseil.html |archivedate=2007-06-13 |df= }}</ref>
