'''Mădăras''' ({{Lang-hu|Madarász}}; {{Lang-sk|Madaras}}) is a [[Communes of Romania|commune]] in [[Bihor County]], [[Romania]], 3&nbsp;km from [[Salonta]], located nearby the [[Hungary|Hungarian]] border - on the [[International E-road network|European road]] [[E671]], and the [[Körös River]] [[canal]]. In 2011, it had 2,828 inhabitants. The commune Hungarian name means "fowler", the Romanian name derives from that as well. It is composed of four villages: Homorog (''Oláhhomorog''), Ianoșda (''Jánosd''), Marțihaz (''Marciháza'') and Mădăras.

Homorog has a [[Romanian Orthodox Church|Romanian Orthodox]] church; built in the 1830s, it is decorated with a valuable [[mural]] from the 1840s.

