'''Stanisław Sówka z Gulczewa''' (of [[Prawdzic Coat of Arms]]), was fourteenth century [[bishop of Płock]] in [[Poland]] who held office from 1367 to 1375 [[Anno Domini|AD]].<ref>[http://www.gcatholic.org/dioceses/diocese/ploc0.htm    Diocese of Płock] at GCatholic.org</ref>

He came from Gulczewa near [[Płock]]  and with his brother Mikołaj worked in the office of the king.<ref>AJ Papierowski, J. Stefanski Płocczanie  Słownik biograficzny(Biographical Dictionary), Plock 2002.</ref> Mikołaj was appointed a bishop by [[pope]] [[Urban V]] a position he filled for 12 years. Following his death Stanislaw was appointed to replace his brother. Stanislaw was in turn succeeded by another brother, Dobiesław Sówka Z Gulczewa who was bishop from 5 July 1375 to the 12th of January 1381.

